-- National Bank of Kuwait Not to Raise Stake in Boubyan Bank, Al-Rai Reports
-- Fiona MacDonald
-- 2010-06-23T05:37:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/national-bank-of-kuwait-not-to-raise-stake-in-boubyan-bank-al-rai-reports.html

          
          
             National Bank of Kuwait, the
country’s largest lender, has no plan at the moment to raise its
stake in Boubyan Bank from 47 percent, Al-Rai  reported , citing
NBK’s Chief Executive Officer for Kuwait Isam al-Sager.  
 The deadline for National Bank of Kuwait from the central
bank to raise its stake in the Islamic lender to 60 percent
expired yesterday and the bank did not request an extension, Al-
Sager said, according to the newspaper.  
